Package: idr2d
Title: Irreproducible discovery rate for genomic interaction
    data
Version: 0.99.1
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given = "Konstantin",
             family = "Krismer",
             role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
             email = "krismer@mit.edu",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8994-3416")),
      person(given = "David",
             family = "Gifford",
             role = c("ths", "cph"),
             email = "gifford@mit.edu",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1709-4034")))
Maintainer: Konstantin Krismer <krismer@mit.edu>
Description: This package measures reproducibility between
    genomic experiments that produce two-dimensional peaks (interactions
    between peaks), such as HiC and ChIA-PET. idr2d is an extension of the
    original idr package, which is intended for (one-dimensional) ChIP-seq
    peaks.
